Analysis of Target Structure  
1. Block Count and Layers  
• The model uses exactly five blocks in three vertical “layers.”  
  – Bottom Layer: A single red arch block.  
  – Middle Layer: Two side‐by‐side cubes (one blue, one red).  
  – Top Layer: An orange triangular “roof” on top of the blue cube, and a yellow half‐cylinder on top of the red cube.  

2. Spatial Arrangement  
• The red arch sits on the ground with its opening facing forward.  
• Directly above the arch is the blue cube, centered on the arch’s top surface.  
• Behind (or to the rear of) the arch is a red cube, sitting level with the blue cube.  
• On top of the blue cube is an orange triangular prism (roof‐shaped).  
• On top of the red cube is a yellow half‐cylinder oriented so that its curved side faces left and right.  

Selection of Dictionary Blocks  
• Red arch (front‐facing opening): index 2  
• Blue cube: index 5  
• Red cube: index 6  
• Yellow half‐cylinder (axis front‐to‐back): index 8  
• Orange triangular roof block (ridge front‐to‐back): index 14  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 2  
  Step2: Move block with index 5  
  Step3: Move block with index 6  
  Step4: Move block with index 8  
  Step5: Move block with index 14  
}
